1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on online social networks and their impact on social behavior, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper explores social behavior in online social networks, which is a key area of research in computational social science.
3. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) - The paper discusses the potential use of findings in privacy management in online social networks, which is a key area of research in cybersecurity and privacy.
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses user behavior in online social networks, which is a key area of research in human-computer interaction.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may fall under this sub-category as it discusses user interaction analysis in online social networks, which may involve multimedia content.
